cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.SE

This paper deals with reasoning about the termination of concurrent programs, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper focuses on fine-grained concurrency, which suggests that it may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The examples used in the paper involve locks, which are commonly used in operating systems (cs.OS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
